  "texts": [
    "However, similar to the point raised for the FP in Fig. 8, this outcome is to be expected.",
    "A negative residual indicates a location where the observed landslide area is lower than the predicted one.",
    "As most of the study site is characterized by grid cells where landslides did not occur, a negative residual points out locations that may not have exhibited landslides in the first place but whose geomorphological characteristics still indicate a likely release of a relatively larger unstable mass in the future.",
    "Ultimately, Fig. 10 shows the constructive and destructive interference between the susceptibility and area density signals.",
    "This leads to isolating landslide-hazardous locations, which appear to be mostly located along the highest portions of the Himalayan range under consideration."
